                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d365">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9200: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-06T17:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 6, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 6—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>248. 1. In the course of an informal conversation with the Minister for Foreign
                    Affairs at the Foreign Office today he said to me “As I told you some time ago
                    Japan does not want war with China. If Chinese central troops which have come to
                    Hopei Province will withdraw there will be no more fighting”.</p>
                <p>2. I took this occasion to say to the Minister as on my own initiative and
                    responsibility that if he ever saw ways by which I could be of help in the
                    situation I hoped he would not fail to let me know.</p>
                <p>3. This informal observation while involving no official commitment of any nature
                    nevertheless indicates to the Minister that if our good offices should ever be
                    desired a channel is open through which he could without embarrassment
                    informally explore the ground.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
